com.github.wuic.nut

Class ByteArrayNut

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.wuic.nut.AbstractNut
      • com.github.wuic.nut.AbstractConvertibleNut
        • com.github.wuic.nut.PipedConvertibleNut
          • com.github.wuic.nut.ByteArrayNut
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConvertibleNut, Nut, Serializable

    public final class ByteArrayNut
extends PipedConvertibleNut
implements Serializable

    Represents an in-memory nut which can be created on the fly in any context.

    This class also aims to provide a fully Serializable Nut. Since the Future implementation which provides the version number could is not always a Serializable, then the version number must be directly provided.

    Since:
    0.2.0
    Version:
    1.7
    Author:
    Guillaume DROUET

      • isDynamic

        public boolean isDynamic()

        Indicates if this nut has a dynamic content, meaning that it could be changed each time Nut.openStream() is invoked. In this case the nut should not be added to any cache and transformation chain should be applied.

        Specified by:
        isDynamic in interface Nut
        Overrides:
        isDynamic in class AbstractConvertibleNut
        Returns:
        true if content is dynamic, false otherwise
